      • onMediaChangeRequested

        void onMediaChangeRequested(Call call,
                            boolean hadAudio,
                            boolean hadVideo)
        A callback notification indicating that a new SDP offer has been received and has switched on or off audio and/or video streaming. Further action is required when audio or video are re-enabled, i.e. deciding whether to un-mute them, as they are automatically kept muted by the API. When this method is called, the Call.hasRemoteAudio() and Call.hasRemoteVideo() values will reflect the new values for audio and video. The previous values for audio and video are passed in as the hadAudio and hadVideo parameters of the method.
        Parameters:
        call - The call that received the media change.
        hadAudio - The previous audio state before the media change.
        hadVideo - The previous video state before the media change.
